We have not changed the use of force policy. We have implemented use of force tracking system and foot chase policy.
We will not rush the implementation of this training. We will take as much time as necessary to increase officer and citizen safety

The goal of these changes is to improve officer and citizen safety, public's trust, awareness and understanding.
Apr thru Oct we will begin implementing curriculum changes. Will re-emphasize policies, philosophies and expected actions.
Timeline: Jan thru April we will confer and evaluate best practices in use of force with other major cities.
Training will begin with the specialized units in the field.
National best practices, officers input, community input and policy compliance will guide development of program.
Major McGee will oversee the program.
Training tactics will include reasonable alternatives, de-escalation and policy compliance in training.
Training in use of force is evolving - adding more sergeants for insight and fresh perspective to training tactics.
Police involved shootings were down 20% in 2013 from 2012.
DPD has also developed a notification protocol w/ the FBI on all officer involved shootings.
